Detailed Description

The section has a list of all the data structures which are exposed to the application.

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct CSI_Cfg_t CSI_Cfg

CSI Configuration.

The structure describes the configuration information which is needed to initialize and setup the CSI Driver.

typedef enum CSI_DataRate_e CSI_DataRate

CSI Data Rates.

Enumeration which describes the data rates supported by the CSI interface.

Please note that the definitions have changed in SDK 2.1/newer releases. Old definitions seemed to imply data rate when it was really the HSClk rate which was twice the data rate The mapping from old values to new values is given below

Defines in SDK 2.0/older Equivalent defines in SDK 2.1/newer (this was actually This is true datarate=[old_define]/2 HSICLK_xxxMhz)

CSI_DataRate_1200Mhz CSI_DataRate_600Mbps CSI_DataRate_900Mhz CSI_DataRate_450Mbps CSI_DataRate_600Mhz CSI_DataRate_300Mbps CSI_DataRate_450Mhz CSI_DataRate_225Mbps CSI_DataRate_400Mhz [invalid/not supported] CSI_DataRate_300Mhz CSI_DataRate_150Mbps CSI_DataRate_225Mhz [invalid/not supported] [No definition] CSI_DataRate_400Mbps

Old definitions in user code will result in compilation error and user should use the above mapping table to find the new definition corresponding to the old one and use that in their code

typedef enum CSI_FIFO_Arbiteration_e CSI_FIFO_Arbiteration

FIFO Arbiteration Mode.

Enumeration which describes the FIFO Arbiteration mode

typedef struct CSI_PhyParams_t CSI_PhyParams

CSI Phy Parameters.

The structure describes the configuration for the PHY registers. This is an advanced configuration feature which is available and can be used by application developers to trim the CSI PHY.

See also
CSI_phyParamsInit
typedef enum CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_e CSI_VC_FIFO_Size

Virtual Channel FIFO Size.

Enumeration which describes the size of the FIFO used by the virtual channels.

typedef enum CSI_VirtualCh_e CSI_VirtualCh

CSI virtual channel.

Enumeration which describes the CSI virtual channels

typedef struct CSI_VirtualChannelCfg_t CSI_VirtualChannelCfg

CSI Virtual Channel Configuration.

The structure describes the configuration which needs to be specified in order to create a virtual channel.

enum CSI_FIFO_Arbiteration_e

FIFO Arbiteration Mode.

Enumeration which describes the FIFO Arbiteration mode

Enumerator
CSI_FIFO_Arbiteration_RR 

Round Robin: This indicates that the FIFO is serviced starting from the lowest enabled virtual channel identifier.

CSI_FIFO_Arbiteration_SEQ 

Sequential: This indicates that the all pending requests from a virtual channel are processed before moving to the next channel.

enum CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_e

Virtual Channel FIFO Size.

Enumeration which describes the size of the FIFO used by the virtual channels.

Enumerator
CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_0 

FIFO Size is 0*33 bits.

CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_32 

FIFO Size is 32*33 bits.

CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_64 

FIFO Size is 64*33 bits.

CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_96 

FIFO Size is 96*33 bits.

CSI_VC_FIFO_Size_128 

FIFO Size is 128*33 bits.
